					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex, Oriental square and semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of approximately 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent rend="visible">50 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>175</height>
										<width>125</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>135</height>
										<width>90</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>50 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 2 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>5 quires of 10 leaves.</p>
									<p>Quires signed with Hebrew letters on the first and last pages.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning.</p>
									<p>A number of pages partially damaged; large signs of book-worming.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="15" writtenLines="15">
									<p>Blank spaces left on folios: 5r, 5v, 10r, 12v and 14v, were intended to be filled up with figures illustrative of the building of the temple.</p>
								</layout>
